title: Loensia fasciata
text:
Loensia fasciata is a species of <a href="Psocoptera">Psocoptera</a> from the <a href="Psocidae">Psocidae</a> family that can be found in <a href="Great%20Britain">Great Britain</a> and <a href="Ireland">Ireland</a>. The species are <a href="yellow">yellow</a>ish-<a href="black">black</a>.
Habitat.
The species feed on <a href="alder">alder</a>, <a href="Ash%20%28Fraxinus%29">ash</a>, <a href="aspen">aspen</a>, <a href="beech">beech</a>, <a href="Cedrus">cedar</a>, <a href="Crataegus%20monogyna">hawthorn</a>, <a href="hazel">hazel</a>, <a href="oak">oak</a>, <a href="pine">pine</a>, <a href="sycamore">sycamore</a>, and <a href="yew">yew</a>. It also likes <a href="apple">apple</a>s.
